  <p class="content"><p>I would be interested to talk to my Cystic Fibrosis  (CF) Doctors. There are others out on the market that are very similar but you can control the pressure it takes to blow into the device. Check out the Accapela and Flutter if you are interested. The Flutter is the more expensive one of the two and I remember it was around ?? gee I got it free with my insurance. This flute looks like you can make it yourself. The real test is to try it out on the CF population since we have the thickest mucouse of the bunch. My favorite by far but not cheap ($ 6000)  to remove mucous from the lungs is the Vest by Hill-Rom Respirtory therapists use these in hospitals now for any one bed ridden. COPD, after surgery etc. I love it and it's just a little bigger than a shoe box. I put my vest on and hook up the hoses and set the pressure and pulse and away I go for 20-60 min. I read, write and best of all God has used this medical device  to keep me alive...I'm 43 years old and if you know anything about CF I'm a miracle! Happy research</p>
</p>
